About

I am currently in the early childhood/childhood education program at St Bonaventure University. My concentration for teaching is in the Math/Science/Technology field. Being a future educator is very important because we are responsible for teaching the future generations how to shape society.

In 2021, I became a gymnastics coach. This made me want to go into the childhood education system because not only was I teaching them new gymnastics skills, but life skills like teamwork and leadership. Seeing their progress and how they all grew as young gymnasts helped me realize what I wanted to do for my carreer.

Bona 101

Bona 101 teaches you everything from what you should know about the history of the school, tips and tricks about resources around campus, and how to prepare yourself for your future at St Bonaventure.

Computer Science 101

The Beauty and Joy of computer science teacher you the basic information of the technological world that surrounds us. Knowing what is happening to the tech that surrounds our everyday lives is extremely beneficial to everyone. This is because you can learn about the truths of AI and the pros and cons of using it in carreers.

Computer Science Lab

In computer science lab you learn the basic functions of how to actually code. Using Snap! you start with the basics of what you need to know about coding. It teaches you how to be patient, while also working on problem solving skills.

Education 101

In education 101 you learn about the basics of the classroom. Every student is different so you learn different teaching styles, how efficient these styles are, and how to manage the classroom.

Math 111

In Math 111 you start with the basics of elementary level math. This is a course needed for childhood education majors to understand how to teach basic math. This aslo teaches you how to spot errors in equations.

Spanish 201

Spanish 201 is a continuation of spansih 101 and 102 which is taught in high school. It focuses on correct grammer and more vocabulary
